          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCH"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The heavy-ion synchrotron at GSI.",
                "The experiments were carried out at the",
                "ALADIN-LAND setup."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "PRJFS"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The radioactive 11Li and 14Be beams were",
                "produced in fragmentation reactions of a primary",
                "18O beam (325 MeV/u), from the heavy-ion synchrotron",
                "at GSI,impinging on an 8 g/cm2 Be target. Separation",
                "of the reaction products according to their magnetic",
                "rigidity was performed with the fragment separator(FRS)",
                "The secondary 11Li beam with an energy of  264 MeV/u,",
                "and 14Be beam with an energy of 287 MeV/u,",
                "were then transferred to a carbon target (thickness",
                "1.29 g/cm2) situated in front of the large-gap",
                "magnetic spectrometer ALADIN."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Carbon target (thickness 1.29 g/cm2)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The deflected charged reaction fragments",
                "were detected in a plasticscintillator wall and",
                "analyzed in coincidence with forward- goingneutrons",
                "from the reaction observed in the large areaneutron",
                "detectorLAND. LAND consists of 200 individual",
                "paddles filling an active volume with a front face",
                "of 200 x 200 cm2 and 100 cm depth."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Tracking results of 0 to 4 neutron detection events",
                "are corrected in terms of the response matrix to",
                "obtain number of 0 to 4 neutron events at LAND",
                "detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
